The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the market close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a third day, losing 0.2
percent to 20,334.85. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.2
percent to 2,695.19.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, fell 1.6 percent to 63 centimos after Energy Minister
Jorge Merino said refineries will cut gasoline prices by as much
as 7 percent tomorrow.  Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1)  (MILPOC1 PE), a zinc and lead producer
controlled by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., slid 1.2
percent to 4.20 soles. The shares dropped after the metals
declined in  London , said Angel Alcala, a trader at Lima-based
Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, rose 0.7 percent to $30.21 after copper advanced in
